Glanders, China
------------
Information received on 26 Aug 2018 from Dr Zhang Zhongqui, Director General, China Animal Disease Control Centre, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing, China (People's Rep. of)

Summary:
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 10 Aug 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 23 Aug 2018
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease in the country
Causal agent: _Burkholderia mallei_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks, total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Equestrian Club, Jiulongpo District, Chongqing
Date of start of the outbreak: 10 Aug 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: other
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Equidae / 17 / 17 / 1 / 16 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 100 / 5.88 / 5.88 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comment: This event was found in an equestrian club by the local Animal Disease Control Center.

Control measures
Measures applied: surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, screening, quarantine, official destruction of animal products, official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste, stamping out, zoning, disinfection, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
China National Glanders Reference Laboratory (National laboratory) / Equidae / gene sequencing / 23 Aug 2018 / Positive
China National Glanders Reference Laboratory (National laboratory) / Equidae / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 23 Aug 2018 / Positive

Future Reporting: the event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

